  saturated fat: 19 g
  carbohydrates: 64 g
  sugar: 13 g
  protein: 49 g
  sodium: 3 g
  serving size: 680
servings: 2
source: https://www.hellofresh.co.uk/recipes/cheesy-nachos-5bc07f4230006c2b844bf972
author: HelloFresh
course: main course
time required: 20 minutes
cuisine: Mexican
---

Lightly oil both sides of each @super soft tortillas with whole wheat{4}. Cut the tortillas into eight equal sized triangles.

> TIP: Lay a couple of the tortillas on top of each other so you can cut more than one at a time!

Pop the triangles onto a large #baking tray{}. Arrange in a single layer. Sprinkle over a pinch of @salt{pinch}. Bake on the top shelf of your #oven{} until lightly coloured, ~{6-8%minutes}.

Meanwhile, halve, peel and thinly slice the @onion{1}(thinly sliced). Heat a splash of @oil{1%splash} in a large #frying pan{} on high heat. Add the onion and @British beef mince{225%g} to the pan. Fry until starting to brown, breaking up the beef with a #wooden spoon{}, ~{5%minutes}. Drain and rinse the @black beans{1%can} in a #colander{}.

Zest and quarter the @lime{1}. Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{30%g}. Add the beans, @garlic clove{1}(minced), @ground cumin{2} and @chilli flakes{1/2%tsp} to the frying pan. Cook for ~{1%minute}. Add a squeeze of lime juice and season to taste with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

> Careful, chilli flakes are hot!

Spoon the beef and bean mixture on top of the nachos (still on the tray!) Sprinkle over the cheese. Bake again on the top shelf of your oven until the cheese has melted, ~{5%minutes}.

Roughly chop the @medium tomato{2}(roughly chopped) into small pieces. Halve the @green pepper{1}(chopped) and discard the core and seeds. Chop into small pieces. Roughly chop the @coriander{1%bunch}(roughly chopped) (stalks and all). Combine the tomato, pepper, coriander and a good pinch of lime zest in a small #bowl{}.

> Add a generous drizzle of @olive oil{1%generous drizzle} and a good squeeze of @lime juice{1%squeeze}. Season to taste with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Remove the nachos from the oven and spoon the tomato salsa over. Dollop a spoonful of @soured cream{150%g} on top along with a sprinkling of remaining lime zest. Serve any spare lime wedges alongside.

Now dig in! Let everyone help themselves! ENJOY!